data.displayName: OMOP Concept Set Version Expression Item
data.description: Individual expression item in the JSON definition of a concept set version (concept_id + three boolean flags for inclusion/exclusion specifications of additional concepts).

includeMapped.description: If true, the expression item will match on the selected OMOP Concept, and all of the Non-Standard OMOP Concepts that map to it. If Include Descendants is also true, then this option will also include all OMOP Concepts that map to the included descendants. Setting this to true enables you to include non-standard Concepts in your Concept Set. Mapping is the process to transform one Concept into a Standard one. Read more: https://ohdsi.github.io/TheBookOfOhdsi/Cohorts.html#conceptSets and https://www.ohdsi.org/web/wiki/doku.php?id=documentation:vocabulary:mapping

includeDescendants.description: If true, the expression item will match on the selected OMOP Concepts and all of its descendants.

isExcluded.description: If true, any concepts matched will be added to the expression as exclusion rather than inclusion criteria. Exclusion criteria take precedence over inclusion criteria, in cases when a single OMOP Concept is affected by more than one entry in the OMOP Concept Set Expression.

koCreatedBy.description: The original author of this knowledge object.
